<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis box="[198,322,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Phenology</emphasis>
. The specimens examined of 
<taxonomicName box="[672,832,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisodrilus">
<emphasis box="[672,832,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">P. anisodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected from February to October, with two abundance peaks in May and July, corresponding to the dry and rainy season, respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
