<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1471,1633]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName box="[344,736,1471,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Photinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisodrilus" subGenus="Paraphotinus">
<emphasis box="[344,736,1471,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Photinus (Paraphotinus) anisodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Figs. 
<number box="[897,940,1471,1494]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
. Dorsal, ventral and lateral view of the aedeagus. Figs. 
<number box="[263,320,1506,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="9.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="5.0">5–14</number>
. Lateral views of the right paramere showing variability (ratio minimum-maximum Depth/Separation), (Figs. 
<number box="[222,265,1540,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
). Lateral view of the right parameres (ratio minimum-maximum WidthBranch/LengthBranch), (Figs. 
<number box="[1381,1424,1540,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
). Lateral view of the right parameres (ratio minimum-maximum WidthTotal/LengthTotal), (Figs. 
<number box="[1192,1248,1575,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
). Lateral view of the right parameral edges: rounded, hooked, truncated, irregular, (Figs. 
